radiographic_examinations.findings: The liver is diffusely echogenic with a smooth contour and no focal liver mass. Intrahepatic biliary ductal dilation with mild common bile duct dilation up to 9 mm. Two stones within the common bile duct, largest measuring 1.1 x 1.4 x 0.7 cm. Gallbladder is distended with mild wall edema and layering luminal sludge. The pancreas is not well visualized.
